Per cent of Employes,'\nOrder Second Cut in Pennsy Pay\nroll.' 'Thirty Thousand Freight\nCars Said to De Idle in Yards.'\nThe people have suddenly becom\nthrifty. The are buying less.\nShort sighted economists propo.\nthai wages should be mt Rut\nthat will pimply reduce the buy\ning pow er of the wage earners and\ntheir dependents, making matters\nworse\nThe excessive profits being\nmade In the great Industrie by\nemployers and linanclers rar ex\nceed any Increases grudgingly\nglveq lo the workers. These ex\nCSSs protlt have been wrung from\nthe consumer, further reducing\nhis buying power Much has been\nr: i.l or tnxinp excess profits\nThere thould be no excess profits\nlo tax.\"\nThe one thing which will bring\nback normal conditions Is a restora\nlion of confidence which will permit\nof liberal buving. While the people\nare Stinting themselves and merchant\nare cleaning their shelves without re\nrowing their Mocks, the factories can\nnot do otherwise than reduce rrWing\ntorceb. The unemployed Immediately\nlo?c their purchasing power and in\nt lm become factors forcing unemploy\nment. The whole process must be re\nereed before the country is out of\nthe slump.\nHi\nNEW JAP BATTLESHIP\nFOUND VERY POWERFUL\nTOKIO Le. 15 (Coriespondence\nof T!k Associated Press. J Japans\nlateat battleship Nagato has a dead\n1gh' tonnage of 23,&0o and can de\n,f,lop peed of 23 knots per hour.\nHer lengih is 660 feet The arma\nment of the new addl lon to the Jap\naneae fleet Includes eight lS-inch\nguns and twenty 6 Inch guns. She Is\nfl ih.i With four turbine engine. The\nNagoto takes a place among the\nlargest battleshipa afloat 1 inlay, her\nItJOO tons comparing with tho Urit\nlah \"Hood\" tl.UO ton and Mi.\nAmerican \"Tenoestee.\" 32.OM0.\nAdmiral Tvchlnai. the commander\nof tbe First njuadron. sld that the\nNagato la unique not only In alse. I\nb-ii also as regards her equipment\nHer main mast is built In the form of\na tower and the range under has\nbeen so deviaed that It ,,n f